## Repo overview

- **Root**: static site with multiple mini-projects. Current home: `index.html`.
- **Main sections**: symmetric difference tool, Operation Car Wash (data viz), Rolling tutorial (Quarto), Pandera tutorial (notebook+HTML), plus external Plotly repo link.

## Entry points

- `index.html`: modern landing page built with Tailwind (CDN), dark mode (localStorage), responsive project grid. Links to:
  - `projects/symmetric-diff/index.html`
  - `projects/lavajato/index.html`
  - `projects/rolling-tutorial/index.html`
  - `projects/pandera-tutorial/index.html`
  - `projects/cardcalc/index.html`
  - External: https://github.com/a0th/plotly

## Subprojects

### Symmetric Difference
- Path: `projects/symmetric-diff/index.html`
- Single-page tool (jQuery) that computes:
  - in A not B
  - in B not A
  - intersection

### Operation Car Wash (Lava Jato)
- Path: `projects/lavajato/index.html`
- Tech: Materialize, D3, DC.js, Crossfilter, Highcharts.
- Data sources: `projects/lavajato/assets/data/*.csv` and texts (`lula.txt`, `esclarecimento.txt`).
- **Note**: Original data source [Meu Congresso Nacional](http://meucongressonacional.com/#mensagem) is no longer available (site paused in 2020). The analysis cannot be reproduced with original data.
- Custom scripts loaded from `projects/lavajato/assets/js/`:
  - `fases.js`, `doacoes.js`, `paral.js`, `citacoes.js`, `cloud.js`, `tagcloud.js`, `colorbrewer.js`.
- Visual sections: phases (warrants), donations, relations (parallel sets), tag clouds, involved counts, citations.

### Rolling Tutorial
- Path: `projects/rolling-tutorial/index.html`
- Generated by Quarto. Assets in `projects/rolling-tutorial/rolling_files/`.
- Demonstrates pandas `groupby(...).rolling()` with Plotly outputs.

### Pandera Tutorial
- Path: `projects/pandera-tutorial/index.html` (and `pandera_tutorial.ipynb`).
- Educational content on Pandera data validation.

### CardCalc
- Path: `projects/cardcalc/index.html`
- Built static app (bundled assets in `projects/cardcalc/assets/`) for a simple card battle damage calculator.

### Imoveis
- Path: `projects/imoveis/index.html`
- Real estate webapp with DuckDB integration, React components, and property data visualization.

## Shared assets

### Styles
- `assets/css/` contains site-wide styles.
- Project-specific styles in `projects/*/assets/css/` (Materialize, Bootstrap, DC.css, resets).

### JavaScript libs and app code
- Root `assets/js/` for site-wide scripts.
- Project-specific libs in `projects/lavajato/assets/js/`:
  - Libraries: `d3.js`, `d3.v3.min.js`, `dc.js`, `crossfilter.js`, `highcharts*.js`, `materialize*.js`, `jquery.js`, `highlight.min.js`.
  - App/init: `init.js` enables Materialize components and parallax.
  - App features: `fases.js`, `doacoes.js`, `paral.js`, `citacoes.js`, `cloud.js`, `tagcloud.js`, `colorbrewer.js`, `gogodrill.js`, `leaflet.tooltip.js`.

### Data
- Lava Jato data in `projects/lavajato/assets/data/`:
  - CSVs: `fases.csv/fases2.csv`, `doacoes.csv/doacoes2.csv`, `envolvidos.csv`, `Partidos.csv`, `Empresas.csv`, `delacoes.csv`, `paralsets.csv`.
  - Texts: `lula.txt`, `esclarecimento.txt`.
- Root `assets/data/` for site-wide data.

